  "root_text": {
    "dhp209:0.1": "Khuddakanikāya ",
    "dhp209:0.2": "Dhammapada ",
    "dhp209:0.3": "Piyavagga ",
    "dhp209:0.4": "Tayojanapabbajitavatthu ",
    "dhp209:1": "Ayoge yuñjamattānaṁ, ",
    "dhp209:2": "yogasmiñca ayojayaṁ; ",
    "dhp209:3": "Atthaṁ hitvā piyaggāhī, ",
    "dhp209:4": "pihetattānuyoginaṁ. ",
    "dhp210:1": "Mā piyehi samāgañchi, ",
    "dhp210:2": "appiyehi kudācanaṁ; ",
    "dhp210:3": "Piyānaṁ adassanaṁ dukkhaṁ, ",
    "dhp210:4": "appiyānañca dassanaṁ. ",
    "dhp211:1": "Tasmā piyaṁ na kayirātha, ",
    "dhp211:2": "piyāpāyo hi pāpako; ",
    "dhp211:3": "Ganthā tesaṁ na vijjanti, ",
    "dhp211:4": "yesaṁ natthi piyāppiyaṁ. ",
    "dhp212:0": "Aññatarakuṭumbikavatthu ",
    "dhp212:1": "Piyato jāyatī soko, ",
    "dhp212:2": "piyato jāyatī bhayaṁ; ",
    "dhp212:3": "Piyato vippamuttassa, ",
    "dhp212:4": "natthi soko kuto bhayaṁ. ",
    "dhp213:0": "Visākhāvatthu ",
    "dhp213:1": "Pemato jāyatī soko, ",
    "dhp213:2": "pemato jāyatī bhayaṁ; ",
    "dhp213:3": "Pemato vippamuttassa, ",
    "dhp213:4": "natthi soko kuto bhayaṁ. ",
    "dhp214:0": "Licchavīvatthu ",
    "dhp214:1": "Ratiyā jāyatī soko, ",
    "dhp214:2": "ratiyā jāyatī bhayaṁ; ",
    "dhp214:3": "Ratiyā vippamuttassa, ",
    "dhp214:4": "natthi soko kuto bhayaṁ. ",
    "dhp215:0": "Anitthigandhakumāravatthu ",
    "dhp215:1": "Kāmato jāyatī soko, ",
    "dhp215:2": "kāmato jāyatī bhayaṁ; ",
    "dhp215:3": "Kāmato vippamuttassa, ",
    "dhp215:4": "natthi soko kuto bhayaṁ. ",
    "dhp216:0": "Aññatarabrāhmaṇavatthu ",
    "dhp216:1": "Taṇhāya jāyatī soko, ",
    "dhp216:2": "taṇhāya jāyatī bhayaṁ; ",
    "dhp216:3": "Taṇhāya vippamuttassa, ",
    "dhp216:4": "natthi soko kuto bhayaṁ. ",
    "dhp217:0": "Pañcasatadārakavatthu ",
    "dhp217:1": "Sīladassanasampannaṁ, ",
    "dhp217:2": "dhammaṭṭhaṁ saccavedinaṁ; ",
    "dhp217:3": "Attano kamma kubbānaṁ, ",
    "dhp217:4": "taṁ jano kurute piyaṁ. ",
    "dhp218:0": "Ekaanāgāmittheravatthu ",
    "dhp218:1": "Chandajāto anakkhāte, ",
    "dhp218:2": "Manasā ca phuṭo siyā; ",
    "dhp218:3": "Kāmesu ca appaṭibaddhacitto, ",
    "dhp218:4": "Uddhaṁsototi vuccati. ",
    "dhp219:0": "Nandiyavatthu ",
    "dhp219:1": "Cirappavāsiṁ purisaṁ, ",
    "dhp219:2": "dūrato sotthimāgataṁ; ",
    "dhp219:3": "Ñātimittā suhajjā ca, ",
    "dhp219:4": "abhinandanti āgataṁ. ",
    "dhp220:1": "Tatheva katapuññampi, ",
    "dhp220:2": "asmā lokā paraṁ gataṁ; ",
    "dhp220:3": "Puññāni paṭigaṇhanti, ",
    "dhp220:4": "piyaṁ ñātīva āgataṁ. ",
    "dhp220:5": "Piyavaggo soḷasamo. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "dhp209:0.1": "Minor Collection ",
    "dhp209:0.2": "Sayings of the Dhamma 209–220 ",
    "dhp209:0.3": "16. The Beloved ",
    "dhp209:1": "Applying yourself where you ought not, ",
    "dhp209:2": "neglecting what you should be doing, ",
    "dhp209:3": "forgetting your goal, you cling to what you hold dear, ",
    "dhp209:4": "jealous of those devoted to their heart’s goal. ",
    "dhp210:1": "Don’t ever get too close ",
    "dhp210:2": "to those you like or dislike. ",
    "dhp210:3": "For not seeing the liked is suffering, ",
    "dhp210:4": "and so is seeing the disliked. ",
    "dhp211:1": "Therefore don’t hold anything dear, ",
    "dhp211:2": "for it’s bad to lose those you love. ",
    "dhp211:3": "No ties are found in they who ",
    "dhp211:4": "hold nothing loved or loathed. ",
    "dhp212:1": "Sorrow springs from what we hold dear, ",
    "dhp212:2": "fear springs from what we hold dear; ",
    "dhp212:3": "one free from holding anything dear ",
    "dhp212:4": "has no sorrow, let alone fear. ",
    "dhp213:1": "Sorrow springs from attachment, ",
    "dhp213:2": "fear springs from attachment; ",
    "dhp213:3": "one free from attachment ",
    "dhp213:4": "has no sorrow, let alone fear. ",
    "dhp214:1": "Sorrow springs from relishing, ",
    "dhp214:2": "fear springs from relishing; ",
    "dhp214:3": "one free from relishing ",
    "dhp214:4": "has no sorrow, let alone fear. ",
    "dhp215:1": "Sorrow springs from desire, ",
    "dhp215:2": "fear springs from desire; ",
    "dhp215:3": "one free from desire ",
    "dhp215:4": "has no sorrow, let alone fear. ",
    "dhp216:1": "Sorrow springs from craving, ",
    "dhp216:2": "fear springs from craving; ",
    "dhp216:3": "one free from craving ",
    "dhp216:4": "has no sorrow, let alone fear. ",
    "dhp217:1": "One accomplished in virtue and vision, ",
    "dhp217:2": "firmly principled, and truthful, ",
    "dhp217:3": "doing oneself what ought be done: ",
    "dhp217:4": "that’s who the people love. ",
    "dhp218:1": "One eager to realize the ineffable ",
    "dhp218:2": "would be filled with awareness. ",
    "dhp218:3": "Their mind not bound to pleasures of sense, ",
    "dhp218:4": "they’re said to be heading upstream. ",
    "dhp219:1": "When a man returns safely ",
    "dhp219:2": "after a long time spent abroad, ",
    "dhp219:3": "family, friends, and loved ones ",
    "dhp219:4": "celebrate his return. ",
    "dhp220:1": "Just so, when one who has done good ",
    "dhp220:2": "goes from this world to the next, ",
    "dhp220:3": "their good deeds receive them there, ",
    "dhp220:4": "as family welcomes home one they love. "
  },
